  <div class="row class-row" id="class-desc">
    <div class="col-lg-4">
      <div class="col-inner">
        <header>
          <h3>Not Cry-It-Out</h3>
        </header>
        <p>
          The first few months of your baby's life are particulary crucial to the establishment of a trusting relationship. Sweet Slumber aims to teach gentle methods of encouraging sleep which respect and nurture your relationship with your baby.
        </p>
        <p>
          The amount of crying necessary for an infant to learn to sleep is dependent on the individual parent/baby couplet, but our mutual goal is to keep it to a minimum.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-lg-4">
      <div class="col-inner">
        <header>
          <h3>Breastfeeding Friendly</h3>
        </header>
        <p>
          Sweet Slumber does not recommend weaning or switching to formula-feeding as effective methods of helping babies to sleep. On the contrary, we strive to develop sleep solutions regardless of your baby's feeding methods.
        </p>
        <p>
          We trust all mamas are feeding their babies with love, and encourage a non-judgemental class environment.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-lg-4">
      <div class="col-inner">
        <header>
          <h3>Personalized Plan</h3>
        </header>
        <p>
          At Sweet Slumber, we believe babies under 4 months need to be eating all night long. Therefore, our workshops are designed for babies aged 4 to 12 months. Within this range, we will tailor an age-appropriate plan to help you and your baby get quality sleep.
        </p>
        <p>
          We are here to support you and your baby on your journey to sweet slumber.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row mobile-show" id="mobile-cta">
    <%= link_to("Find a Class", workshops_path, class: 'btn btn-default') %>
  </div>
</div>
